HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 56
BY REPRESENTATIVE TURNER
A RESOLUTION
To designate March 24, 2026, as Louisiana Athletic Trainers Day at the capitol and to
commend the members of the Louisiana Athletic Trainers Association (LATA) for
their dedicated hard work on behalf of the athletes of Louisiana.
WHEREAS, LATA members are skilled healthcare professionals trained in the
prevention, emergency management, evaluation, and therapeutic intervention of
sports-related injuries and conditions; and
WHEREAS, the mission of the national association is to represent, engage, and foster
the continued growth and development of the athletic training profession and athletic trainers
as unique healthcare providers; and
WHEREAS, athletic training is an allied healthcare profession recognized by the
American Medical Association, and certification in the profession requires strict educational
standards based on specific knowledge and skills; certified athletic trainers have a long
history of providing quality healthcare for athletes and individuals engaged in physical
activity; and
WHEREAS, citizens of Louisiana are allowed to participate in meaningful and
rewarding athletic competitions throughout the state and nation as a result of the hard work
of the men and women of LATA; and
WHEREAS, the members of LATA are most deserving of the highest recognition
for their dedicated work.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the members of the Louisiana Athletic
Trainers Association for their outstanding achievements; does hereby recognize and record
